Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into small 2cm chunks 
(no need to peel!). Place on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over a glug of @olive oil{}
and season with @salt{}. Toss together and pop on the top shelf of your oven. 
Roast until soft and slightly crispy round the edges, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn 
halfway through cooking.

Halve, then remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 2cm pieces. 
Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve the 
@green chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the seeds and finely chop. Drain the 
@red kidney beans{1 can} in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water.

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the pepper and cook 
until softened, ~{5-6%minutes} more. Add the chilli (add less chilli if you're 
not a fan) along with the @ground cumin{2%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and half 
the coriander. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the 
@chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), kidney beans and 
@water{75%ml}. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2}.

Lower the heat slightly and simmer until reduced by half and is thick and 
tomatoey, ~{15%minutes}. Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into 1cm cubes). 
Remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and thinly slice.

Zest the @lime{1/2} and pop into a #mixing bowl{}, squeeze in the lime juice. Add 
the olive oil (see ingredients for amount), a pinch of salt and @ground black 
pepper{pinch} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Whisk together 
with a #fork{} and set aside. Add the tomato and lettuce and toss just before 
serving.

Spoon the chilli mixture into an #ovenproof dish{}. Remove the sweet potato from 
your oven and set the grill to high. Arrange the sweet potato on top of the 
chilli mixture and sprinkle over the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}. Pop under 
your #grill{} until the cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}. Share between your 
plates and serve the salad on the side. Finish with a sprinkling of the 
remaining coriander. Enjoy!